## Review System

Code is reviewed automatically via hooks. Review mode configured at bootstrap:

- **Review mode**: _TBD_ (commit-only / per-edit-only / both / none)
- **Per-edit guard**: `readonly-guard.sh` blocks writes to protected files
- **Post-edit**: `auto-format.sh` — auto-runs project formatter after every edit
- **Safety**: `safety-net.sh` — blocks destructive commands (`rm -rf`, `git push --force`, etc.)
- **On stop**: `test-gate.sh` — runs the test suite before Claude finishes a task
- **Alternative review**: `/qwen-review` skill — local Qwen2.5-Coder via Ollama (airgapped)

## Project Wiki

The context-keeper maintains a persistent wiki at `docs/wiki/`. This is the synthesized
knowledge base for the project — not a collection of individual docs, but interconnected
pages that compound with every task.

**For all agents**: Read `docs/wiki/index.md` at task start. Read pages relevant to your
domain before exploring code. The wiki is pre-synthesized knowledge — faster and more
complete than re-discovering from source. If you find stale wiki content, flag it in
your output so the context-keeper can fix it.

